        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 7:03PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 703 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Darrouzett, or 7 miles north of Lipscomb, moving
southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lipscomb.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
